metadata.name: E R E B U S #239
metadata.description:
Fragments of minds

Our daily life is filled with automatisms, habits that make our comfort zone. Then one day an event occurs that touches us deeply. We step out of our comfort zone, an internal emotional tornado is unleashed in our consciousness. This work tries to illustrate this flow of passion, this emotional violence on the fabric of daily life.

About features.
There are 3 random characteristics:

1. Latent state of mind
This feature correspond to the lines in the background. ‚ÄòHealthy‚Äô is the most frequent, and the other types appear more rarely (‚ÄôPsychotic‚Äô is really rare).

2. Crystallization

This feature corresponds to the strength of the flow of the passion in our mind. Probability : ‚ÄòNormal‚Äô = 77%, ‚ÄòStrong‚Äô = 33%.

3. Disturbance
The disturbance rate is ‚ÄôLow‚Äô (frequent), or ‚ÄòHigh‚Äô (rare).

When a work is collected, a process of synchronicity is triggered. Synchronicity is a process of randomness that allows us to communicate with our unconscious (psychological paradigm) or with the hidden forces of the universe (spiritual paradigm). The rarer an image is, the more it represents an exceptional psychic state.

To print a high resolution image (resolution is 6400*6400px.), press [p].
To print a screen resolution image, right-clic then ‚Äòsave image‚Äô.

This artwork celebrate the anniversary of FxHash - Happy Birthday little baby :-)
50% of primary sales are donate to the Processing Foundation (thank you for making my days better).

Artwork by @GenerativePunk.

metadata.name: fx(mandala) #48
metadata.description:
Outer mandalas represent the universe or world-system and are traditionally offered as thank you gifts. In this case it‚Äôs my offering to the fxhash community as a celebration of #fxhashturnsone. 

SOME MINTS WILL BE GOLDEN TICKETS
A golden ticket AND the iteration directly before it will each receive a free 8 x 10in special edition signed physical made from 12 layers of laser cut museum board. 

Physicals for all mints can be requested and/or claimed at https://alleditions.art

Outer Mandalas is part of a broader series I am working on that explores the use of techniques and patterns from sacred geometries using generative randomness. I use generative algorithms to create ‚Äúblueprints‚Äù that can be transferred out of the physical realm and into the real world as multi-layered three dimensional sculptures. 

I create limited edition physical ‚Äúprints‚Äù for Outer Mandalas by using a high powered laser to precisely cut through 4-ply museum boards (the same stuff you frame a picture with) to create 12 unique layers. I then stack and carefully glue each layer together in order to create a dynamic relief that plays with light and shadow. These pieces are visually engaging artworks that tend to spark conversation whenever they are seen.  

A big thank you to the fxhash platform team and all the passionate collectors and generative artists I‚Äôve met over the past year. It‚Äôs been my honor to be a part of this amazing community. 

s to save as a layered SVG 
p to save as a PNG
e to explode the layers
Click and drag the mouse to change the shadows. 

This generative is VERY intensive and probably won‚Äôt render very well on a mobile device.

metadata.name: stigmergy #36
metadata.description:
Stigmergy is a method of decentralized organization in which agents communicate by leaving traces in a shared environment. This piece simulates a kind of stigmergy among a large population of particles. Each particle leaves a trail behind it as it moves, and determines its direction of motion based on the trails around it. The rules for how a particle should move based on its surroundings were created with a user-guided evolutionary process.

Press "c" to capture a 2048x2048 image of the simulation. You can also press the spacebar to pause/unpause the simulation, and press "n" while paused to move the simulation forward a single step.

as a java-applet. now; not working in most browsers any more. '__'
